40|$|On a cool September evening {{somewhere in}} America in 1940, a family gathers around a vacuumtube radio. As someone adjusts the tuning knob, a {{distinct}} and serious voice {{cuts through the}} airwaves: “This … is London. ” And so begins <b>a</b> riveting <b>firsthand</b> account of the infamous “London Blitz, ” the wholesale bombing of that city by the German air force in World War II. Behind the microphone, sitting atop a London rooftop thousand...|$|R
