500|$|My Life in Orange: Growing Up {{with the}} Guru is {{an account of}} {{a child growing up}} in the Rajneesh {{movement}} led by Bhagwan Shree Rajneesh. The book is <b>a</b> <b>firsthand</b> account, written by Tim Guest at the age of 27, [...] years after his experiences. The book was published in 2004 by Granta Books. The book's title is a reference to the term [...] "the orange people", which was used to refer to members of the Rajneesh movement due to the color they dyed their clothes.|$|E
